SEVERAL people were injured following a shooting at an informal settlement in Isipingo on Thursday afternoon.According to Netcare 911 s Chris Botha reports from the scene indicate that unknown gunmen opened fire on people in the informal settlement in Old Main Road opposite Pilgrim Railway Station. Exact detail to the incident will however form part of a police investigation. After the wounded were triaged it was found that three people died, one was in a critical condition, and five sustained serious injuries. The injured are being treated at the scene and were transported to various hospitals, he said. SAPS is investigating. - Supplied. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.